                    <span>I think Jim Rogers is a very interesting person..  When I saw him on Bloomberg News I was compelled to buy this book..  When I got to the book store I was a little distressed after not being able to find the Barnes & Noble book store I called in the phone book..  
<br />
<br />When I finally found Hot Commodities on the book shelf I was at first unimpressed and started to put it back on the shelf.. Looking around there wasn't a lot of books on the subject so I decided I better get the book.  Immediatly you'll notice it doesn't have a lot of pictures and is written in black & white.. If your like me you want a little color particularly in the form of pictures & diagrams.  There are some diagrams but it basically all literature.  
<br />
<br />A picture paints a thousand words...  Well in this case Jim has a lot more to say about commodities than can be summed up in a picture.  Needless to say I liked the book and it's worth buying..  I read from cover to cover in 2 days and liked nearly every prospective that was presented.  I was supprised to find that he gained his knowledge not just by reading but by actually going to differnt countries and learning the societies that influence commodities.  
<br />
<br />This is not a book on technical analysis it's a book about commodities from a supply & demand perspective and secular trends of.</span>
                  
